1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3067 By: Pogemiller
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to initiative and referendum;
amending 34 O.S. 2021, Section 25, which relates to
8 special elections; modifying powers of Governor with
respect to special election dates; and providing an
9 effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 34 O.S. 2021, Section 25, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 25. Whenever any measure shall be initiated by the
16 people in the manner provided by law, or whenever the referendum
17 shall be demanded against any measure passed by the Legislature,
18 same shall be submitted to the people for their approval or
19 rejection at the next regular election that falls on the first
20 Tuesday in November; provided, the Governor shall have power, in his
21 or her discretion, to call a special election to vote upon such
22 questions, or to designate the mandatory primary election as a
23 special election for such purpose before the first Tuesday in
24 November; and, the official ballot title and measure is transmitted
Req. No. 14406 Page 1

1 from the Secretary of State to the State Election Board not fewer
2 than seventy (70) days from the date of the next General Election
3 pursuant to Section 12-116 of Title 26 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
4 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
